<title>UK: HSBC names new U.S. chief economist.</title>
<headline>HSBC names new U.S. chief economist.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-09-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>HSBC Holdings plc said on Monday Ian Shepherdson, chief UK economist at HSBC Markets Ltd in London, has been appointed chief economist at HSBC Securities Inc in New York with effect from October 14.</p>
<p>Shepherdson will be responsible &quot;for the analysis and forecasting of the U.S. economy for the HSBC Group and for the marketing of the Group's global economic view to clients,&quot; HSBC said.</p>
<p>He replaces Lacy Hunt, whose departure has already been announced.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom 44 171 542 2774</p>
